task.summary: Created a component that is initialized when a project is opened, screams "I'm alive"
Created a component that is initialized when a project is opened, screams "I'm alive"
Now have fused actions and components together into GatherData class
Now have a prototype of a method to access the message strings in IntelliJ's message system. Also added most of the useful things I've learned to do with IntelliJ's plugin SDK.
Finally have output of all messages. Used the text exporter class to obtain the whole text. It will need to be parsed but it's very structured, even tabbed out.
Now runs in PyCharm, however the right click menu doesn't show our action...
Pressing the help button opens google.com
Pressing the help button now opens first google result from search term typed into prompt
Moving over from Java to Python: Side window help button opens a URL Still need to work on GatherData action, it doesn't take python right now
